Connect micro USB to use USB/terminal based control of software

Setting of terminal: echo = OFF, key emulation: only CR, DTR = OFF, RTS = OFF


Commands

5) "display"
Prints some measurements

1) pw xx
Sets the pulse width on both channels to xx

2) "pwl xx" and "pwr xx"
Sets the pulse width on the left and right channels to xx

3) "auto"
Pulse width on left and right channels will ramp automatically

4) "manual" 
Opposite of 'Auto" - changes the mode to manual pulsewidth changes

5) "rf_ascii"
Sets the serial ISR to handle the serial data as ascii.

6) "rf_binary"
Sets the serial ISR to handle the serial data as binary.